articles.title: H5N1 Bird Flu: Aussie Toddler, With Travel History To Kolkata, Tested Positive, Was Kept In Intensive Care - News18
articles.description: The WHO said this is the first confirmed human infection caused by avian influenza A to have ever been reported by Australia.
articles.content:
A two-and-a-half-year-old girl tested positive for H5N1 bird flu and needed hospital intensive care treatment in Australia after travelling to India, the World Health Organization said on Friday.
